  "body": "*Title*: *Add names and alias to resource*\r\n\r\n*Description*:\r\nIn xDS, every resource has a name that\u2019s used to identify the resource. Currently, this resource name is implemented in the individual protocol i.e. VirtualHost, RouteConfig, Listener, etc. I propose that we add a resource name to the Resource message in order to create a common place for the resource names passed in the xDS protocol. In designing the virtual host discovery service, we\u2019ve also found that there is a potential for aliases to the names of resources. In the case of the virtual host discovery service, each of the domains constitutes a separate alias.\r\n\r\nTo handle these cases, I propose extending the message Resource to match the following: \r\n\r\nmessage Resource {\r\n  // The resource level version. It allows xDS to track the state of individual\r\n  // resources.\r\n  string version = 1;\r\n\r\n  // The resource being tracked.\r\n  google.protobuf.Any resource = 2;\r\n\r\n  //The name of the resource being tracked\r\n  string name = 3;\r\n\r\n  //Aliases of the resource name\r\n  repeated string aliases = 4;\r\n}\r\n\r\n\r\n[optional *Relevant Links*:]\r\n",
